Profile:  Ultra Slim Compact CarryCondition:  Pristine!  (Not sure if I ever fired it)
Super-compact 40 S&W pistol that easily fits into a pocket or waistband.
Striker-fired action.  Trigger system is like a true double action/single action design.  It is fired single action every time, and the double action is there as a backup, in the event that a cartridge fails to fire on the first pull of the trigger.  In other words, the trigger system has double-strike capability. The slide does not have to cock the action before the trigger can be pulled again, allowing the shooter to try again if a dud cartridge does not fire on the first pull. Trigger pull is perfect for its size.
Multiple safeties:  Manual safety allows the pistol to be carried cocked and locked by blocking the trigger and locking the slide.  There is a trigger safety, so carrying with the thumb safety in the “off safe” position will work as well.  There is also an internal firing pin block, that blocks the striker from reaching the primer of the chambered cartridge unless the trigger is in its rearward position.
3 dot sight system.   Rear sight is adjustable for both elevation and windage. 
Grip well-textured for a positive hold and shaped for a comfortable feel.
Low-profile magazine release -- large enough for a quick reload, but is not so elevated above the surface of the frame that it might be unintentionally activated.
Barrel is 3.28” and provides excellent accuracy for such a small pistol.* Includes original plastic box from factory and paper work.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Custom Winchester .308 Sniper Rifle w/ART II Vietnam Era Military Optic
postcontent: For sale I have a really clean Custom Winchester Model 70 Sniper Rifle with a rare ART II Military Sniper scope. This is a very accurate setup where a lot of money has been spent. The receiver is an early Winchester model 70 that was produced around 1970. The barrel is a custom piece that is fluted and built very heavily. The stock is a Custom coated textured finish that is Gray with black and white specks. The Optic is a rare and highly sought after original Leatherwood ART II (Adjustable Ranging Telescope) that was used in the late Vietnam Era on the M40 Sniper Rifles. It does have an adjustable ranging Cam for a .308. It sits on the original base that is required for the Optic to perform properly with Auto Ranging Technology. The scope is serial numbered as well to verify its authenticity. These Optics command a premium when they do come up for sale on the open market. This setup is in great shape and is very accurate. I have hit the same hole twice with two consecutive shots at over 100 yards with it in the past. I’m only listing it simply because I don’t have the time or real estate to enjoy the yardage and time that this gun deserves. It has a very light but crisp, tight trigger pull. It also includes a nice Harris Ultralight adjustable bipod as well. This piece is very fun to shoot and is definitely very reliable. If you have any questions, please feel free to ask. If I can't answer, leave a message and I'll return your call. Thanks for looking!Dustin 270-317-4376
